              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>CORDELIA MINSTER</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Necromancer</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">18 to 22</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, North</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Wizard spires near stone (loc +500 +2275)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">18 to 24</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Be careful at level 18 to 20 because Cordelia is harder than she cons.  She is a Bard, but although she does not use songs on you she hits like a monk.  But if you are careful she can be beaten at those levels.  If you do not want to risk death then wait until level 20 because from 20 to 24 she is pretty easy.
<br><br>
Basically you use the standard DoT-Pet-Fear-Nuke strategy. First hit her with Darkness and then run a little ways to get her away from the Spires and Tower.  If you do not do this then there is a chance that the Patrolling Guard Fredrick will come along and he will help Cordelia if he sees you fighting her.  If you want to be even more cautious pull her all the way to the West Karana zone border.  It is not too far and will provide a good escape route, but you will need to practice a few times to learn exactly where the border is.  After you pull her to your spot send in the pet and start applying the DoTs.  I used Heat Blood, Heart Flutter, Darkness and Poison.  By now she is on top of you and very angry.  Cast fear until it sticks then nuke her with you best Lifesuck spell.  I did not try conserve mana here, I just wanted to kill her before fear wore off because she hits pretty hard.
<br><br>
Up until level 20 I had to use Shieldskin and my other buffs every time and even then it was close.  You may also need to feign death sometimes to get her off of you.  But from 20 on none of that is needed.  I also use Dark Pact (or Allure of Death if you have it) right before every fight to get mana back during the fight. You are Lifedraw/Siphoning anyway and once when the fight was close the extra mana let me cast one more Lifedraw and that saved my life.
<br><br>
The loot she drops varies a lot but on average is pretty good.  She drops a lot of Raw-Hide armor which is worth around 7gp to the gypsies in the zone.  She also drops Words and Pearl Shards but not very often.  The money loot ranges from 12cp to 2.5pp. Not bad for her level.
<br><br>
But the best thing about her is the XP.  I would guess that you get about 1 bubble of exp for killing her 6 times.  And since she spawns about every 5 minutes you can level pretty fast here.  If you run out and get a Scythe Beetle in between pulls the XP is really fast.  I camped her off and on for a few days and got very good XP and in all that time I never had to share her with anyone.  I guess only necros are willing to take the faction hit for killing her. (-Antonican Bards, -Qeynos Guards, -Knights of Truth, +Ring of Scale, +Mayong Mistmoore).
<br><br>
One more thing, she spawns right next to the Wizard Spire and stands there for a few minutes.  But if you do not attack her fast enough she takes a tour of the zone.  Basically she follows the path around the zone and finally stops just outside of the building with the 2 bartenders in the Northwest corner of the zone.  So if you miss her at the spires just head due north until you see the building on the path and wait.  She will soon walk up and stand next to the tree that is standing there.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Flec Romancer (The Tribunal)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>9</b> (average of <b>3</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><