face="Tahoma">...be aware to have enough to drink and eat with you. Without any friends in the zone you will be quick at a point when every slot is full with one instrument or/and you will be out of food and drink. No merchant will sale anything to you. What I did was running down to and bind me in the underground. Whenever my bags were overloaded again I gated down there. So I was able to take min. food and drink to hava max. room for the loot.

Be safe
DDS</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="center"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><A HREF="hgmessage.asp?Guide=19">Post a Message</A></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="center"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><A HREF="hunting.asp">Browse other guides</A></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="center"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><A HREF="submithg.asp">Submit a Hunting Guide</A></font></td></tr></div></center>
       
